.TH MU2EDAQ_NOTIFY_CPP 3 "July 2026" "mu2edaq-notify 0.1.0" "Mu2e DAQ"
.SH NAME
mu2edaq_notify_cpp \- C++17 publisher library for the Mu2e DAQ
notification server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
#include <mu2edaq_notify/notify.hpp>
// link: -lmu2edaq_notify -lcurl   (CMake: mu2edaq::notify)

mu2edaq::notify::Options opts;   // server_url, token, source, host,
                                 // timeout_ms, discover
mu2edaq::notify::Publisher pub(opts);
bool ok = pub.publish(severity, title, message, meta);
pub.debug(t,m)  pub.info(t,m)  pub.warning(t,m)
pub.error(t,m)  pub.critical(t,m)

std::string url = mu2edaq::notify::discover_server(timeout_s);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Publishes events over HTTP using libcurl. Server resolution order:
Options::server_url, $MU2EDAQ_NOTIFY_URL, then a mu2edaq-discovery
multicast query (UDP 239.255.42.99:28999, filter app=notify) when
Options::discover is true. The bearer token comes from Options::token
or $MU2EDAQ_NOTIFY_TOKEN.
.PP
publish() returns true when the server accepted the event; it never
throws on delivery failure. Meta is a
std::map<std::string,std::string>.
.SH BUILDING
.nf
cmake -S . -B build && cmake --build build
ctest --test-dir build     # CppUnit tests when CppUnit is installed
.fi
Works on Linux, macOS, and Windows 11 (MSVC; links ws2_32
automatically).
.SH SEE ALSO
mu2edaq_notify(3), mu2edaq-notify-server(1)
